<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="441" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1418,2021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1418,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The salient features of the new species include: aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[928,1056,1419,1445]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Figs 10–13</figureCitation>
) with two spinose processes; ventral margin of periandrium with a blade-shaped spinose process at basal 1/3 (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1105,1455,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); dorsal margin of endosoma with a large spinose process, not furcate (
<figureCitation box="[606,689,1491,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); middle of right part of endosoma with a laminal process (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1422,1491,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); apical 1/2 of left side and apical part of periandrium with multiple small teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1117,1527,1553]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="443" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1418,2021]" box="[199,1183,1562,1590]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1563,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Measurements.</emphasis>
Body length: male 
<quantity box="[602,737,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" unit="mm" value="6.3" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="5.9">5.9–6.7 mm</quantity>
(N = 24), female 
<quantity box="[938,1073,1563,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.45" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="6.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" unit="mm" value="7.45" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="6.6">6.6–8.3 mm</quantity>
(N = 16).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1418,2021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1598,1625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[700,802,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellow, ocelli faint yellow, semi-translucent. Antenna, vertex, face and rostrum generally yellowish white. Pronotum generally yellowish white. Mesonotum light brown. Forewing semi-translucent, costal vein with three small spaced dark brown spots; slightly behind stigma, middle part of forewings and behind clavus with an irregular puce spot respectively, near claval fork with a triangular yellow spot, basal and middle part of forewings with two inner oblique yellow stripes; apical half of wing with brown patches. Hind tibiae yellow. Ventral abdomen yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1418,2021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1815,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[514,618,1815,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) 0.9 times wider than long; anterior margin nearly straightly, posterior margin U-shaped recessed, median carina absent. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[787,854,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) 2.9 times as long as wide. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1385,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) 2.4 times longer than vertex; posterior margin recessed in a right angle. Mesonotum 1.4 times longer than pronotum and vertex combined. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[476,575,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[190,1397,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Andixius cultratus sp. nov., male 1. Dorsal view; 2. Lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, ventral view; 5. Forewing; 6. Genitalia, lateral view; 7. Pygofer and gonostyli, ventral view; 8. Anal segment, dorsal view; 9. Gonostyli, lateral view; 10.Aedeagus, right side; 11. Aedeagus, left side; 12. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 13.Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (1–4, 6–13); 1.0 mm (5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
) 2.4 times longer than wide, with twelve apical cells and six subapical cells; RP 3 branches, MP with 5 terminals: MP 
<subScript attach="right" box="[602,618,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">11</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[671,687,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">12</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="right" box="[741,749,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">2</subScript>
, MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[802,810,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">3</subScript>
, and MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[910,918,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">4</subScript>
, fork MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1024,1032,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">1</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1089,1097,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">2</subScript>
basad of fork MP 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1295,1303,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">3</subScript>
+MP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1359,1367,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">4</subScript>
. Hind tibia with six lateral spines, usually small; chaetotaxy of hind tarsi: 8/8, 2nd hind tarsus with three platellae.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907666" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3907666" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907666/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="442" startId="2.[151,264,1896,1921]" targetBox="[202,1391,185,1862]" targetPageId="2">
